===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
Uncertain.

Possibly a {{liushu|p|nocap=yes}} of a woman with a headdress. Cognate to {{zh-l|*女}} with {{zh-l|*辛}} on top, though in the modern form the headdress has simplified to unrelated {{zh-l|*立}}.

Alternatively, may be an {{Han compound|辛|女|t1=torture device|t2=woman|ls=ic|nocap=y}} – female criminal.

===Etymology===
Cognate to {{och-l|捷|victory; booty}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}). See there for more.

